</div>
</div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6 vc_custom_1459086197645"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  What is NXIVM">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>NXIVM is a community guided by humanitarian principles that seek 
to empower people and answer important questions about what it means to 
be human. The NXIVM philosophy is expressed through a series of 
companies and initiatives, all of which were designed to broaden the way
 we currently think about problems, and to help create solutions for a 
kinder, more sustainable, ethical world. With unique tools that 
facilitate success, both internally and externally, NXIVM helps people 
realize the potential that exists within them.</p>
<blockquote><p>
<em>“Alone we can do so little; together we can do so much.”</em></p>
<p style="text-align: right; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">– Helen Keller</p>

		</blockquote></div>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div data-ewf-full-width="true" data-ewf-full-width-init="true" class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1514933722475" style="padding-left: 33px; padding-right: 33px; position: relative; left: -33px; box-sizing: border-box; width: 1236px;"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="headline blanco"><h3>Founder</h3><h6>Keith Raniere</h6></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row-full-width"></div><div data-ewf-full-width="true" data-ewf-full-width-init="true" class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1514933841953" style="padding-left: 33px; padding-right: 33px; position: relative; left: -33px; box-sizing: border-box; width: 1236px;"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-8"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  vc_custom_1517979209710">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>Keith Raniere has devoted his life to studying the complex issues 
that face our modern world, and to developing tools to enhance the human
 experience through community, social action, science, technology and 
education.</p>
<p>Raniere has founded multiple companies focusing on increasing joy and ethics in the world. Under the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.nxivm.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.nxivm.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1516831167656000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFisRTVKGCUPOGoJy6rh-lJQ6TV9w">NXIVM</a>&nbsp;umbrella,
 he has developed a series of educational models that offer integrative 
solutions to complex subjects such as gender, relationships, childhood 
development, mind-body complex, compassionate ethics, and creative 
expression. These initiatives range from an award-winning performing 
arts company to an early childhood education that promotes cultural, 
linguistic, emotional, physical and problem-solving potential.</p>
<p>He founded&nbsp;<a href="http://www.executivesuccessprograms.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.executivesuccessprograms.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1516831167656000&amp;usg=AFQjCNE-TMZhKQKRWMuMJu4z4L6OaoUQwg">Executive Success Programs</a>, Inc. (ESP) in 1998 with&nbsp;<a href="http://nancysalzman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://nancysalzman.com&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1516831167656000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFZzrgVc7Og9qX3HSuCA7KJAifMGA">Nancy Salzman</a>,
 one of the world’s top trainers in personal and professional 
development, seeking to advance ethics, humanity, and critical thinking 
on an individual and global scale. One of the cornerstones of ESP 
is&nbsp;<em><a href="http://rationalinquiry.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://rationalinquiry.org/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1516831167656000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFv2esl79-gdMziYTR0Gt4mgm31vQ">Rational Inquiry®</a></em>,
 Raniere’s patent-pending technology that provides a scientific process 
for achieving peak human performance. Most recently, these tools 
successfully have been applied to treating neurobiological disorders 
with unprecedented results. In partnership with the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ethicalsciencefoundation.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.ethicalsciencefoundation.org/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1516831167656000&amp;usg=AFQjCNELxIwf668-DypvfooZPcbsCyhp0w">Ethical Science Foundation</a>,
 several people have been helped to overcome severe cases of Tourettes 
Syndrome, with plans to study the potential on other conditions.</p>
<p>Some of his most passionate and&nbsp;purposeful work can be seen in 
the peace movement he founded in Mexico, where gang violence, corruption
 and poverty are at crisis levels.&nbsp;<a href="http://inlakech.mx/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">InLaK’ech</a>
 (an expression that translates to “you are the other me”) has been 
credited with initiatives that promote community, inspire leadership 
within small villages, and provide systems to disable violence and stop 
perpetrators. He sees the struggles faced by the Mexican people as a 
metaphor for the world, and hopes to inspire the possibility for peace.</p>
<p>To learn more about Keith Raniere, his ideas, initiatives and ideology, visit&nbsp;<a href="http://keithraniere.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://keithraniere.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1515178618845000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHbUEMu1wW6LBPPvbGvjm8Fdnmgzg">his website</a>.</p>
<p><strong><a href="http://www.nxivm.com/letter-from-the-co-founder/">LETTER FROM KEITH RANIERE ON CURRENT SITUATION</a></strong></p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-4"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_left">
		
		<figure class="wpb_wrapper vc_figure">
			<div class="vc_single_image-wrapper   vc_box_border_grey"><img src="Home%20%E2%80%93%20NXIVM_files/nxivm_keith_raniere.jpg" class="vc_single_image-img attachment-full" alt="" width="864" height="864"></div>
		</figure>
	</div>
</div></div></div><div class="vc_row-full-width"></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1459122201809"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="wpb_wrapper"><div class="headline "><h3>Companies</h3></div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_custom_1459121433342"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6 vc_custom_1459121889078"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_single_image wpb_content_element vc_align_left  vc_custom_1522536093099">
		
		<figure class="wpb_wrapper vc_figure">
			<div class="vc_single_image-wrapper   vc_box_border_grey"><img src="Home%20%E2%80%93%20NXIVM_files/NXIVM-Grid-3.jpg" class="vc_single_image-img attachment-large" alt="" width="940" height="500"></div>
		</figure>
	</div>
</div></div><div class="spaceitdamnit wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-6 vc_custom_1518133668154"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element  vc_custom_1515362985959">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p>Society, government, religion, family—all human systems are made 
up of people. Large-scale change must therefore&nbsp;find its root in 
the individual. If we are to create a noble civilization, this 
transformation must begin by looking inward.</p>
<p>NXIVM is a new ethical understanding that allows you to create an 
internal framework that reflects your best self, and offers the 
resources to manifest that vision into a reality. It allows you to 
explore your most fundamental nature and begin to redirect your power of
 creation, a power that we all possess in a very human sense. The NXIVM 
philosophy is expressed through its various companies, their 
contributions, and, most importantly, the individuals who work together 
to create a better world.</p>
<p>All of these companies and social movements were conceptualized&nbsp;by NXIVM’s founder, Keith Raniere.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
<a href="http://www.nxivm.com/companies/" class="btn " style="">Click here to explore</a></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element ">
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">

			function revslider_showDoubleJqueryError(sliderID) {
				var errorMessage = "Revolution Slider Error: You have some jquery.js library include that comes after the revolution files js include.";
				errorMessage += "<br> This includes make eliminates the revolution slider libraries, and make it not work.";
				errorMessage += "<br><br> To fix it you can:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1. In the Slider Settings -> Troubleshooting set option:  <strong><b>Put JS Includes To Body</b></strong> option to true.";
				errorMessage += "<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2. Find the double jquery.js include and remove it.";
				errorMessage = "<span style='font-size:16px;color:#BC0C06;'>" + errorMessage + "</span>";
					jQuery(sliderID).show().html(errorMessage);
			}

function checkSearchForm()
{
if(document.getElementById('site-search-input').value == "Search" || document.getElementById('site-search-input').value == "")
{

document.getElementById('site-search-input').focus();
return false;

<section class="section2"><div class="pagemn">
<a id="nothought" name="nothought"></a><div class="lampbgimage">
<a href="javascript:%20stopStartNoThought();">
<img alt="Listen" title="Listen" src="OSHO%20%7C%20Meditation%20-%20Mindfulness%20and%20the%20Science%20of%20the%20Inner_files/mute_icon.png" id="speakerJwPlayer"></a><p>
<a href="http://bit.ly/NoThoughtAndroidWeb" target="_blank">

<img src="OSHO%20%7C%20Meditation%20-%20Mindfulness%20and%20the%20Science%20of%20the%20Inner_files/apple_app_btn.png"></a></p></div><div class="lampbg"> <strong>No-Thought for the Day <sup>®</sup></strong><div class="region region-thought-of-the-day"><div id="block-osho-custom-thought-of-the-day" class="block block block-osho-custom"><div class="content"> This moment is given to you, a gracious gift from God or the whole <br>or whatsoever you want to call it — Tao, dhamma, logos.<br>This moment is available to you: sing a song, live it in its totality.<br>And don´t try to sacrifice it for any other moment<br> that is going to
come in the future. <br>Live it for its own sake.<div id="jwplayerdiv" style="visibility: hidden;"><div class="jwplayer playlist-none" id="player" style="width: 480px; height: 270px; background-color: var click = 1;
function stopStartNoThought()
{
if(click == 1)
{
jwplayer("player").play();
click = 0;
jQuery("#speakerJwPlayer").attr('src','/sites/all/themes/osho/images/listen_icon.png' );
}
else
{

click = 1;
jQuery("#speakerJwPlayer").attr('src','/sites/all/themes/osho/images/mute_icon.png' );
}
}
jQuery("#jwplayerdiv").css('visibility', 'hidden');
</script>

<script type="text/javascript">
jQuery(document).ready(function(){
function getCookie(c_name)
{
var i,x,y,ARRcookies=document.cookie.split(";");
for (i=0;i<ARRcookies.length;i++)
{
x = ARRcookies[i].substr(0,ARRcookies[i].indexOf("="));
y = ARRcookies[i].substr(ARRcookies[i].indexOf("=")+1);
x = x.replace(/^\s+|\s+$/g,"");
if (x == c_name)
{
return unescape(y);
}
}
}
function setCookie(c_name,value,exdays)
{
var exdate = new Date();
exdate.setDate(exdate.getDate() + exdays);
//var c_value = escape(value) + ((exdays == null) ? "" : "; expires = "+exdate.toUTCString()) + "; domain = .; path =/ ";
var c_value = escape(value) + ((exdays == null) ? "" : "; expires = "+exdate.toUTCString()) + "; path =/ ";
document.cookie = c_name + "=" + c_value;
}
function checkCookie(c_name)
{
var c_value = getCookie(c_name);
if (c_value == null || c_value == "undefined" || c_value == '' )
{
//cookie not found
return false;
}
else
{
//cookie found
return true;
}
}
var checkPopup = checkCookie('iosho-offer-popup-cookie');
//var checkPopup = getCookie('iosho-offer-popup-cookie');
console.log(checkPopup);
if(jQuery('.messages.error').length == 1){
checkPopup = false;
}
console.log(checkPopup);
if(!checkPopup)
{
setCookie('iosho-offer-popup-cookie', '30', 30);
var pop = ouibounce(document.getElementById('ouibounce-modal'),{
aggressive: false,
timer:0,
callback: function() { console.log('ouibounce fired!'); }
});
_gaq.push(['_trackEvent', 'Popup', 'Show Popup', 'Home Page: OPEN ACCESS to OSHO On-Line Library']);
pop.fire();
pop.disable();
jQuery('body').click( function() {
jQuery('#ouibounce-modal').hide();
});
jQuery('#ouibounce-modal #pop_cls').click(function() {
jQuery('#ouibounce-modal').hide();
});
jQuery('#ouibounce-modal .modal').click(function(e) {
e.stopPropagation();
});
if(jQuery('.messages.error').length == 1 )
{
var $pop_error = jQuery('.messages.error').html();
//increase height of popup while error
var $new_popup_height = jQuery('.messages.error ul li').length * 16 + 34 + 415;
jQuery('.messages.error').remove();
jQuery("#pagemn1").prepend('<div class="messages error">'+$pop_error+'</div>');
jQuery("#ouibounce-modal .modal").css("height",$new_popup_height + "px");
}
}else{
console.log('pop not called');
}
});
</script>
